{"id":11903,"date":"2022-06-30T13:22:19","date_gmt":"2022-06-30T11:22:19","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/?p=11903"},"modified":"2022-06-30T14:51:41","modified_gmt":"2022-06-30T12:51:41","slug":"national-council-chairperson-lauds-election-of-new-pap-president","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/national-council-chairperson-lauds-election-of-new-pap-president\/","title":{"rendered":"National Council Chairperson Lauds Election of New PAP President"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Zimbabwean Chief, Fortune Charumbira was elected as the new President of the Pan-African Parliament (PAP) late Wednesday evening (29 June 2022). Charumbira\u2019s election was widely celebrated in Southern Africa as he is first person from the sub-region to lead PAP.<\/p>\n<p>Although he was the sole presidential candidate, running for PAP presidency requires the support of at least 50 percent plus one (50% + 1) of votes. According to a National Council Secretariat member at the event, Charumbira won a total of 161 votes out of 231 cast. Thirty-one members abstained while 11 ballots were spoilt.<\/p>\n<p>Charumbira\u2019s election was largely due to the implementation of the rotation principle. The principle of rotation provides for the PAP presidency to rotate among the five regions of the AU, namely north, west, east, central and Southern Africa. The principle is followed by all AU organs as a means to unite the continent. Due to previous dominance of the east, west and central regions in the PAP, the southern and northern African regions were the only ones eligible to nominate candidates for the presidency this time around as they are the only regions that had not held the presidency since PAP\u2019s inception in 2004.<\/p>\n<p>National Council chairperson, Hon. Lukas Sinimbo Muha duly congratulated the newly elected PAP President and further commended the PAP membership for adhering to the principle of rotation, citing that it was an imperative mechanism for democracy to thrive and for good governance for the continental Parliamentary body.<\/p>\n<p>While the AU had agreed on the rotation principle, it is yet to be ratified by PAP and legally it is still not enforceable. However, AU Commission Chairperson, Moussa Faki Mahamat, Mahamat, who facilitated the PAP elections, pleaded with PAP delegates to give the two regions a chance to lead the institution, in what he termed to be \u201cin the spirit of fair play.<\/p>\n<p>Accepting his election, Chief Charumbira told delegates that his focus would be on cleaning up the public image and uniting the African diaspora, including strengthening the fight against corruption.<\/p>\n<p>Before his election, Chief Charumbira has served as one of PAP\u2019s four vice-presidents since 2018. He is a traditional leader and a Zimbabwean Member of Parliament. Chief Charumbira was the Southern African Development Community&#8217;s (SADC) candidate.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Zimbabwean Chief, Fortune Charumbira was elected as the new President of the Pan-African Parliament (PAP) late Wednesday evening (29 June 2022). Charumbira\u2019s election was widely celebrated in Southern Africa as he is first person from the sub-region to lead PAP. Although he was the sole presidential candidate, running for PAP presidency requires the support of&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":8,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[159,39],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-11903","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-home-page-slider","category-news","category-159","category-39","description-off"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/11903","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http